data.chText: （重要事情或时刻的）高潮，极点，顶点
data.enText: the most exciting or important event or point in time
the climax of his political career

data.chText: （戏剧、音乐等通常接近结束时出现的）高潮
data.enText: the most exciting part of a play, piece of music, etc. that usually happens near the end
the highest point of sexual pleasure

data.chText: 达成（或形成）极点（或顶点、高潮）
data.enText: to come to or form the best, most exciting, or most important point in sth

data.chText: 星期天的音乐盛会将把这次会演推向高潮。
data.enText: The festival will climax on Sunday with a gala concert.

data.chText: 那项引起轰动的裁决使长达六个月的审判达到了高潮。
data.enText: The sensational verdict climaxed a six-month trial.

means: (戏剧、音乐等通常接近结束时出现的)高潮
达成(或形成)极点(或顶点、高潮)

tr: the moment of most intense pleasure in sexual intercourse
the decisive moment in a novel or play
example: the deathbed scene is the climax of the play

tr: arrangement of clauses in ascending order of forcefulness
the highest point of anything conceived of as growing or developing or unfolding
example: the climax of the artist's career
in the flood tide of his success

tr: the most severe stage of a disease
end, especially to reach a final or climactic stage
example: The meeting culminated in a tearful embrace

value.def: The climax of something is the most exciting or important moment in it, usually near the end.

example.ex: For Pritchard, reaching an Olympics was the climax of her career...
example.tran: 对普里查德来说，参加奥运会是她事业上的巅峰。

example.ex: It was the climax to 24 hours of growing anxiety...
example.tran: 24小时里不断加重的焦虑在那一刻达到顶点。

example.ex: The last golf tournament of the European season is building up to a dramatic climax.
example.tran: 欧洲赛季的最后一场高尔夫球锦标赛就要迎来最激动人心的时刻。

value.tran: (通常临近结尾的)高潮，最精彩处

value.def: The event that climaxes a sequence of events is an exciting or important event that comes at the end. You can also say that a sequence of events climaxes with a particular event.

example.ex: The demonstration climaxed two weeks of strikes...
example.tran: 游行示威将持续了两周的罢工推向了高潮。

example.ex: They've just finished a sell-out UK tour that climaxed with a three-night stint at Brixton Academy.
example.tran: 他们刚刚结束在英国的巡回演出，演出场场爆满，最后在布里克斯顿学院进行的为期3天的演出将此次活动推向了高潮。

value.def: When someone climaxes, they have an orgasm.

example.ex: Often, a man can enjoy making love but may not be sufficiently aroused to climax.
example.tran: 通常情况下，男人可能会享受鱼水之欢，但未必能完全达到高潮。
